('- Useful pattern: `do.call(rbind', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'list_of_dfs)` to combine a list of data frames.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `Reduce(f', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'x)` applies binary function `f` cumulatively: `Reduce(""+"', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `Filter(f', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'x)` keeps elements where `f(elem)` is `TRUE`. Unlike `x[sapply(x', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
