('- `Find(f', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'x)` returns the **first** element where `f(elem)` is `TRUE`. `Find(f', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `Position(f', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'x)` returns the **index** of the first match (like `Find` but returns position', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `lengths(x)` returns the length of **each element** of a list. Equivalent to `sapply(x', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'length)` but faster (implemented in C).', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `tryCatch` **unwinds** the call stack — handler runs in the calling environment', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'not where the error occurred. Cannot resume execution.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `tryCatch(expr', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'error = function(e) e)` returns the error condition object.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `tryCatch(expr', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'warning = function(w) {...})` catches the **first** warning and exits. Use `withCallingHandlers` + `invokeRestart(""muffleWarning"")` to suppress warnings but continue.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Custom conditions: `stop(errorCondition(""msg"', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'class = ""myError""))` then catch with `tryCatch(...', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Returns `TRUE` or a **character string** describing the difference — NOT `FALSE`. Use `isTRUE(all.equal(x', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'y))` in conditionals.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `modifyList(x', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'val)` replaces elements of list `x` with those in `val` by **name**.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- **Does** add new names not in `x` — it uses `x[names(val)] <- val` internally', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'so any name in `val` gets added or replaced.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Inverse of `unlist`: given a flat vector and a skeleton list', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'reconstructs the nested structure.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `relist(flesh', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'skeleton)` — `flesh` is the flat data', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Update with `setTxtProgressBar(pb', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'value)`. Close with `close(pb)`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Style 1: rotating `|/-\`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'style 2: simple progress. Only style 3 shows percentage.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `format(object.size(x)', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'units = ""MB"")` for human-readable output.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `vignette()` lists all vignettes; `vignette(""name"', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'package = ""pkg"")` opens a specific one.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `stl` requires `s.window` (seasonal window) — must be specified', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'no default. `s.window = ""periodic""` assumes fixed seasonality.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `decompose`: simpler than `stl`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'uses moving averages. `type = ""additive""` or `""multiplicative""`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Factor indexing: `x[f]` uses integer codes of factor `f`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'not its character labels. Use `x[as.character(f)]` for label-based indexing.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Data frame `[` with single column: `df[', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '1]` returns a **vector** (drop=TRUE default for columns)', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Matrix indexing a data frame (`df[cbind(i', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'j)]`) coerces to matrix first — avoid.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `subset` argument uses **non-standard evaluation** — column names are resolved in the data frame', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'which can silently pick up wrong variables in programmatic use. Use `[` with explicit logic in functions.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- On a **data frame**', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '`apply` coerces to matrix via `as.matrix` first — mixed types become character.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Returns an **array** (not a data frame). Class info on return values is **discarded** (e.g.', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'Date objects become numeric).', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `...` args to FUN are **not** divided into cells — they apply globally', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'so FUN should not expect additional args with same length as X.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Default `by` is `intersect(names(x)', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'names(y))` — can silently merge on unintended columns if data frames share column names.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `by = 0` or `by = ""row.names""` merges on row names', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'adding a ""Row.names"" column.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- If `f` is a list of factors', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'interaction is used; levels containing `"".""` can cause unexpected splits unless `sep` is changed.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `cbind` on data frames calls `data.frame(...)`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'not `cbind.matrix`. Mixing matrices and data frames can give unexpected results.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `rbind` on data frames matches columns **by name**', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'not position. Missing columns get `NA`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `cbind(NULL)` returns `NULL` (not a matrix). For consistency', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '`rbind(NULL)` also returns `NULL`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Result is always an **array** (even 1D)', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'class ""table"". Convert to data frame with `as.data.frame(tbl)`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `duplicated` marks the **second and later** occurrences as TRUE', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'not the first. Use `fromLast = TRUE` to reverse.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- For data frames', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'operates on whole rows. For lists', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Atomic vectors recycle to match longest column', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'but only if exact multiple. Protect with `I()` to prevent conversion.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Duplicate column names allowed only with `check.names = FALSE`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'but many operations will de-dup them silently.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `as.numeric(f)` returns **integer codes**', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'not original values. Use `as.numeric(levels(f))[f]` or `as.numeric(as.character(f))`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `c()` on factors unions level sets (since R 4.1.0)', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'but earlier versions converted to integer.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Levels are sorted by default', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'but sort order is **locale-dependent** at creation time.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Returns columns named after the grouping variables', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'with result column keeping the original name.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- If FUN returns multiple values', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'result column is a **matrix column** inside the data frame.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Returns a **permutation vector** of indices', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'not the sorted values. Use `x[order(x)]` to sort.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Default is ascending; use `-x` for descending numeric', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'or `decreasing = TRUE`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- For character sorting', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'depends on locale. Use `method = ""radix""` for locale-independent fast sorting.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `as.numeric(diff', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'units = ""hours"")` to extract numeric value in specific units.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `options(scipen = n)`: positive biases toward fixed notation', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'negative toward scientific. Default 0. Applies to `print`/`format`/`cat` but not `sprintf`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `options(digits = n)`: significant digits for printing (1-22', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'default 7). Suggestion only.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `options(warn = n)`: -1 = ignore warnings', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '0 = collect (default)', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `options(OutDec = "', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '")`: change decimal separator in output (affects `format`', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `options(contrasts = c(""contr.treatment"', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '""contr.poly""))`: default contrasts for unordered/ordered factors.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `list.files(pattern = ""*.csv"")` — `pattern` is a **regex**', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'not a glob! Use `glob2rx(""*.csv"")` or `""\\.csv$""`.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- On some filesystems', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '`ctime` is status-change time', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `file_test(""-f"', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'path)`: TRUE if regular file exists.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `file_test(""-d"', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'path)`: TRUE if directory exists.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Returns a **list** (one element per input string)', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'even for a single string.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `URLencode(url', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'reserved = FALSE)` by default does NOT encode reserved chars (`/`', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `I()` is required to use arithmetic operators literally: `y ~ x + I(x^2)`. Without `I()`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '`^` means interaction crossing.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `model.matrix` creates the design matrix including dummy coding. Default contrasts: `contr.treatment` for unordered factors', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '`contr.poly` for ordered.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Column names from `model.matrix` can be surprising: e.g.', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '`factorLevelName` concatenation.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Default `family = gaussian(link = ""identity"")` — `glm()` with no `family` silently fits OLS (same as `lm`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'but slower and with deviance-based output).', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Common families: `binomial(link = ""logit"")`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '`poisson(link = ""log"")`', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `weights` in `glm` means **prior weights** (not frequency weights) — for frequency weights', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'use the cbind trick or offset.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `anova(glm_obj', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'test = ""Chisq"")` for deviance-based tests; `""F""` is invalid for non-Gaussian families.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- Quasi-families (`quasibinomial`', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', '`quasipoisson`) allow overdispersion — no AIC is computed.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
('- `aov` is a wrapper around `lm` that stores extra info for balanced ANOVA. For unbalanced designs', 'From awesome-chatgpt-prompts community collection', 'Type I SS (sequential) are computed — order of terms matters.', 'chatgpt', 1, ARRAY['community', 'chatgpt', 'prompts'], 'General use'),
